# Copy to .env and fill in. Never commit .env (see .gitignore).
# v1 (walk) — the platform. The zero-key paths (GitHub *public* repos, OP Mainnet reads) run
# with NONE of these set; fill them in for the full keyed example.

# --- Connector credentials (resolved centrally via the credential registry; never read ad hoc) ---
# GitHub: public repos work with NO token (rate-limited). A read-only PAT lifts the rate limit.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
# Onchain: a public OP Mainnet RPC is used by default (no key). Override to your own provider:
# OP_MAINNET_RPC_URL=

# Slack: a bot token (xoxb-…) with channels:history; SLACK_CHANNEL is the channel ID to read.
# SLACK_TOKEN=
# SLACK_CHANNEL=C0123ABCD
# Notion: an internal integration token; share the pages/DB with the integration. No target needed.
# NOTION_TOKEN=
# Monday: a personal/API v2 token; MONDAY_BOARD_ID is the board to read items from.
# MONDAY_TOKEN=
# MONDAY_BOARD_ID=

# --- Shared memory (Postgres + pgvector; brought up via docker-compose) ---
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://beacon:beacon@localhost:5432/beacon
# Embeddings provider for semantic recall (optional; a local deterministic stand-in is used if unset).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# --- Runtime ---
LOG_LEVEL=info
BEACON_ENV=local
